===Etymology===
{{bor+|zh|aav}}; compare {{cog|mkh-pro|*Йҹhaam|*Йҹhaam ~ *Йҹhiim|blood}}, whence {{cog|km|бһҲбһ¶бһҳ||blood}}, {{cog|mnw|бҖҶбҖ®|tr=chim|t=blood}}, {{cog|mkh-ban-pro|*bhaЛҗm||blood}}, {{cog|mkh-kat-pro|*К”ahaam||blood}}, {{cog|mkh-khm-pro|*maЛҗвӮҒm||blood}}. Chinese has final ''-ЕӢ'' because initial and final ''m'' are mutually exclusive ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2003}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

This word's rare occurrence in a traditional saying indicates that it is not part of the active vocabulary of OC, but a
survival from a substrate language.

